HEADWORD: Errantry
<hw>Er"rant*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
wandering; a roving; esp., a roving in quest of adventures.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The employment of a knight-errant.</def>
